  <p>Block 7 introduces the unit's signature AI partner — <a href="/ai-partners/stakeholder-voice/">The Stakeholder Voice</a>. Today's central T/T move: <strong>counter-argument work</strong>. Students identify the strongest counter to their stakeholder's position, then respond without strawmanning. The Stakeholder Voice AI role-plays the opposing stakeholder, making the strongest version of their argument — students rehearse responding to a well-formed opposite position rather than a caricature. Section A students who've been building their Boodle Build bot have an additional move today: bring the bot to a peer for stress-testing.</p>
